ce:section.ce:para:
For verification the chemical composition of the synthesized quantum dots, FT-IR (Fig. 4
                        ), 1HNMR & 13CNMR (
                           Supplementary data
                        ) spectral data were analyzed. FT-IR spectral data were plotted for xanthan before and after its exploitation in clustering of the desirable quantum dots. From FT-IR analysis, all of the tested colloids were shown with the characteristic peaks of xanthan [48], as all the spectral maps were exhibited with prominent band at 3505 cm−1, corresponding to OH groups that shared in hydrogen bonding, while, the peaks at 2871 cm−1 and 2344 cm−1 are assigned to C-H stretching vibrations of the –CH2 groups in the xanthan gum. Moreover, a significant band for carbonyl group (1587 cm−1), –CH2 asymmetric (1417 cm−1) bending, C-C aliphatic chain vibration (1323 cm−1), glycoside linkage between monomers of xanthan (1018 cm−1), and pyranose ring characteristic band (763 cm−1). However, after exploiting of xanthan in nucleation of CDs, the significant bands of carbonyl group & C-C aliphatic chain vibration were shown with lower intense and that for C-C aliphatic chain vibration & C-H stretching vibrations of the –CH2 groups were completely disappeared. Whereas, a new peak was detected for all the analyzed colloids of CDs with and without metal doping at 925 cm−1, that is significant for C-C aromatic chains vibration and another band corresponds to C-O-C was detected at 760 cm−1. These could affirm that; metal doping did not affect on the conjugative/aromatic composition of the prepared CDs.
